# Cloudflare Pages headers file — copied verbatim to dist/ root by Vite (from public/).
# https://developers.cloudflare.com/pages/configuration/headers/
#
# IMPORTANT: the CSP script-src list below is a set of exact sha256 hashes of the
# inline <script> blocks in index.html (theme picker, dataLayer init, gtag init,
# YM_COUNTER_ID, Yandex Metrika init). If you edit the text of ANY of those inline
# scripts, their hash changes and the browser will silently block the script under
# this CSP. Regenerate after any edit: npm run build && node scripts/csp-hashes.mjs
# then paste its output (one 'sha256-...' per line) into the script-src list below.
# (The browser normalizes CRLF to LF before hashing script content per the HTML
# spec, so a naive hash of the raw file bytes won't match — that script handles it.)
# Adding a new analytics pixel (Meta/TikTok/Clarity) from the commented templates in
# index.html requires adding both its hash here AND its script/connect domains below.
# CI enforces this automatically (scripts/verify-csp-hashes.mjs, run in .github/workflows/
# build.yml after the build step) — a forgotten hash now fails the build instead of shipping
# a silently-broken script to production. NOTE: that guard only checks the root
# dist/index.html — en/, vi/, and community/*/index.html are NOT auto-verified, only
# manually (see 2026-07-21 session notes). Most of their inline scripts are byte-identical
# to the root copy (same hash, nothing to add), except community/index.html's language
# auto-detect block, which is deliberately DIFFERENT (redirects to /community/en//vi/, not
# /en//vi/ — real bug fixed 2026-07-21) and has its own hash below.

